<refentry version="5.0-subset Scilab" xml:id="imminmaxloc" xml:lang="en" xmlns="http://docbook.org/ns/docbook" xmlns:scilab="http://www.scilab.org">
<refnamediv><refname>imminmaxloc</refname><refpurpose>Compute per-channel extrema and their first locations.</refpurpose></refnamediv>
<refsynopsisdiv><title>Syntax</title><synopsis>[minValue, maxValue, minLocation, maxLocation] = imminmaxloc(im)</synopsis></refsynopsisdiv>
<refsection><title>Description</title><para><function>imminmaxloc</function> returns per-channel minimum and maximum values with first [row column] locations.</para></refsection>
<refsection><title>Examples</title><programlisting role="example"><![CDATA[
im = uint8([0 10; 20 30]);
[lo, hi, loLoc, hiLoc] = imminmaxloc(im);
]]></programlisting></refsection>
